{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782402618950,"sessionID":"ses_1008692e3ffes7wyEd1LjsXTmN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_h3K7jN2IbNL9K8KSJVQsGYwh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\current-agent-input.md","limit":260},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\current-agent-input.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Agent Input Brief - phase-04-home-history-discovery / coverage-repair\n2: \n3: This brief is a narrow planning input compiled from current workflow reports. It is not an authority file.\n4: Start here, then open only the referenced source paths, target endpoints, capabilities, or reports needed for the task.\n5: \n6: ## Boundaries\n7: \n8: - Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n9: - Target project: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n10: - Translation inputs: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs`\n11: - Do not read sibling old translations unless the user explicitly asks for comparison.\n12: - Edit only target project files and agent-maintained authority files required by the current session.\n13: \n14: ## Freshness\n15: \n16: | artifact | exists | generatedAt | phase | error |\n17: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n18: | phaseTaskChecklist | yes | 2026-06-25T15:44:55+00:00 | phase-04-home-history-discovery |  |\n19: | phaseGroupVerdicts | yes | 2026-06-25T15:50:06+00:00 | phase-04-home-history-discovery |  |\n20: | phaseCapabilityChecklist | yes | 2026-06-25T15:20:14+00:00 | phase-04-home-history-discovery |  |\n21: | translationQualitySummary | no |  |  | missing |\n22: | phaseCoverageGate | yes | 2026-06-25T13:48:00+00:00 | phase-04-home-history-discovery |  |\n23: | targetStructure | yes | 2026-06-25T15:44:55+00:00 |  |  |\n24: | sourceCoverageMatrix | yes | 2026-06-25T02:01:25+00:00 |  |  |\n25: | platformCapabilityCheck | yes | 2026-06-25T02:01:25+00:00 |  |  |\n26: \n27: ## Scope Rules\n28: \n29: - Treat the current implementation group contract as the primary task input.\n30: - Open the listed source paths and target endpoints before consulting broad phase reports.\n31: - Use full phase reports as indexed references; do not sweep unrelated groups unless this group requires a small shared foundation.\n32: - Update authoritative matrix/capability rows only for this group and any directly required shared surface.\n33: \n34: ## Working Set\n35: \n36: - clusters: _none_\n37: - repair child groups: _none_\n38: - implementation groups: `phase-04-home-history-discovery-source-behavior-presentation-home`\n39: - features: `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-085460c333-001-image-viewing-bitmap-exif-handling-zoom`, `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-75e43540b7-002-intent-uri-bundle-deeplink-or-cross-scre`, `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef2f599530-003-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o`, `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-5415bc8d6b-006-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata`, `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-73b7c6cb19-004-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`, `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef0657c4ea-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat`\n40: - capabilities: _none_\n41: - source paths: `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreen.kt`\n42: - target endpoints: _none_\n43: - acceptance evidence: Closed critical/high features must record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence.; Build pass alone is not per-feature verification.\n44: \n45: ## Current Implementation Groups\n46: \n47: | group | priority | type | title | sources | target domains |\n48: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n49: | phase-04-home-history-discovery-source-behavior-presentation-home | critical | source-behavior | Source behavior: presentation/home | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreen.kt |  |\n50: \n51: ## Plan Contract Alignment\n52: \n53: Plan contract entries are upstream planning evidence. Use them to preserve phase/group ownership, but resolve conflicts through source code and authority JSON records.\n54: - summary: planGroups=2, matchedGroups=2, unmatchedGroups=0\n55: \n56: ### Matched Plan Groups\n57: \n58: | plan group | priority | type | matched groups | source methods | risks | acceptance |\n59: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n60: | phase-04-home-content | critical | source-behavior | phase-04-home-history-discovery-source-behavior-presentation-components, phase-04-home-history-discovery-source-behavior-presentation-home, phase-04-home-history-discovery-verification-phase-tests-and-evidence | Home, HomeViewModel.onEvent, TopSection, AdSection | Do not push home-specific state into the global shell.; Search and filter controls are visible behavior even without backend filtering. | Target tests verify selection command ordering.; Build gate passes for phase-04-home-history-discovery. |\n61: \n62: ## Current Group Contract\n63: \n64: ### `phase-04-home-history-discovery-source-behavior-presentation-home` Source behavior: presentation/home\n65: \n66: - priority/type: `critical` / `source-behavior`\n67: - source paths: `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreen.kt`\n68: - feature ids: `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-085460c333-001-image-viewing-bitmap-exif-handling-zoom`; `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-75e43540b7-002-intent-uri-bundle-deeplink-or-cross-scre`; `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef2f599530-003-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o`; `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-5415bc8d6b-006-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata`; `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-73b7c6cb19-004-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`; `app